#part2

Data Preparation

Load and Preprocess Data

# Create simulated dataset with all districts
set.seed(123)
n <- 1500

# Define Guangzhou main administrative districts
districts <- c("Tianhe", "Yuexiu", "Haizhu", "Liwan", "Baiyun", 
               "Huangpu", "Panyu", "Huadu", "Nansha", "Zengcheng", "Conghua")

simulated_data <- data.frame(
  TransactionDate = seq(as.Date("2021-01-01"), by = "day", length.out = n),
  Layout = sample(c("2 bedroom1 living_room", "3 bedroom2 living_room", 
                   "4 bedroom2 living_room"), n, replace = TRUE),
  Area = round(runif(n, 50, 200), 1),
  Orientation = sample(c("North", "South", "East", "West"), n, replace = TRUE),
  Floor = sample(c("Low", "Middle", "High"), n, replace = TRUE),
  District = sample(districts, n, replace = TRUE, 
                   prob = c(0.15, 0.12, 0.13, 0.08, 0.14, 
                           0.09, 0.11, 0.06, 0.05, 0.04, 0.03)),
  UnitPrice = round(runif(n, 10000, 60000), 0)
)

# Data preprocessing
simulated_data <- simulated_data %>%
  mutate(
    BedroomCount = as.numeric(gsub("([0-9]+).*", "\\1", Layout)),
    LivingRoomCount = as.numeric(gsub(".*bedroom([0-9]+).*", "\\1", Layout)),
    LivingRoomCount = ifelse(is.na(LivingRoomCount), 1, LivingRoomCount),
    Orientation = as.factor(Orientation),
    Floor = as.factor(Floor),
    District = as.factor(District)
  )

cat("Data preprocessing completed! Final data dimensions:", dim(simulated_data))
## Data preprocessing completed! Final data dimensions: 1500 9

District Overview

# District descriptive statistics
district_summary <- simulated_data %>%
  group_by(District) %>%
  summarise(
    Observations = n(),
    Mean_Price = round(mean(UnitPrice), 2),
    SD_Price = round(sd(UnitPrice), 2),
    Mean_Area = round(mean(Area), 2),
    Avg_Bedrooms = round(mean(BedroomCount), 2),
    Price_Per_SQM = round(mean(UnitPrice) / mean(Area), 2),
    .groups = 'drop'
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    Proportion = round(Observations / nrow(simulated_data) * 100, 1),
    District = factor(District, levels = District[order(-Mean_Price)])
  ) %>%
  arrange(-Mean_Price)

# Stratified Regression Analysis

Build Independent Regression Models for All Districts

# Build independent regression models for each district
district_models <- simulated_data %>%
  group_by(District) %>%
  group_modify(~ {
    model <- lm(UnitPrice ~ Area + BedroomCount + LivingRoomCount + 
                  Orientation + Floor, 
                data = .x)
    
    # Extract model results
    tidy_model <- broom::tidy(model) %>%
      mutate(
        r_squared = summary(model)$r.squared,
        adj_r_squared = summary(model)$adj.r.squared,
        n_obs = nrow(.x),
        .before = 1
      )
    
    return(tidy_model)
  })

cat("=== All District Regression Models Analysis Completed ===\n")
## === All District Regression Models Analysis Completed ===
cat("Total districts analyzed:", n_distinct(district_models$District), "\n")
## Total districts analyzed: 11

Model Performance Comparison

# Extract model performance metrics
model_performance <- district_models %>%
  group_by(District) %>%
  summarise(
    R_squared = first(r_squared),
    Adj_R_squared = first(adj_r_squared),
    Observations = first(n_obs),
    .groups = 'drop'
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    R_squared = round(R_squared, 4),
    Adj_R_squared = round(Adj_R_squared, 4)
  ) %>%
  arrange(-R_squared)

# Extract all key variable coefficients
key_coefficients <- district_models %>%
  filter(term %in% c("Area", "BedroomCount", "LivingRoomCount", 
                     "FloorMiddle", "FloorHigh")) %>%
  mutate(
    term = factor(term,
                  levels = c("Area", "BedroomCount", "LivingRoomCount", 
                            "FloorMiddle", "FloorHigh"),
                  labels = c("Area\n(RMB/sq.m)", "Bedroom Count\n(RMB/room)", "Living Room Count\n(RMB/room)", 
                            "Middle Floor\n(vs Low)", "High Floor\n(vs Low)")),
    significance_star = ifelse(p.value < 0.001, "***",
                              ifelse(p.value < 0.01, "**",
                                    ifelse(p.value < 0.05, "*", ""))),
    estimate_rounded = round(estimate, 1)
  )

# Create heatmap
ggplot(key_coefficients, aes(x = District, y = term, fill = estimate)) +
  geom_tile(color = "white", size = 0.5) +
  geom_text(aes(label = paste0(estimate_rounded, significance_star)), 
            color = "black", size = 3) +
  scale_fill_gradient2(low = "blue", high = "red", mid = "white", 
                      midpoint = 0, 
                      name = "Coefficient Value") +
  labs(
    title = "Housing Price Factor Coefficients Heatmap by District",
    subtitle = "Color indicates coefficient size, *p<0.05, **p<0.01, ***p<0.001",
    x = "Administrative District",
    y = "Influencing Factors",
    caption = "Note: Coefficient unit is RMB, floor variables use low floor as reference"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
        axis.text.y = element_text(size = 9))

Key Findings Summary by District

cat(" Deep Analysis of Housing Price Influencing Factors by District \n\n")
##  Deep Analysis of Housing Price Influencing Factors by District
# Create summary table
significant_factors_summary <- district_models %>%
  filter(p.value < 0.05 & term != "(Intercept)") %>%
  group_by(District, term) %>%
  summarise(
    Coefficient = round(first(estimate), 2),
    PValue = round(first(p.value), 4),
    .groups = 'drop'
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    Effect = ifelse(Coefficient > 0, "Positive", "Negative")
  )

# Display significant factors by district
for(district in unique(simulated_data$District)) {
  
  district_data <- district_models %>% filter(District == district)
  performance <- model_performance %>% filter(District == district)
  sig_factors <- significant_factors_summary %>% filter(District == district)
  
  cat("- ", district, "\n")
  cat("Model Performance: R =", round(performance$R_squared, 3), 
      "(Adj R =", round(performance$Adj_R_squared, 3), ")\n")
  cat("Sample Size:", performance$Observations, "properties\n")
  
  if(nrow(sig_factors) > 0) {
    cat("Significant Influencing Factors:\n")
    for(i in 1:nrow(sig_factors)) {
      cat("  -", sig_factors$term[i], ":", sig_factors$Effect[i], 
          "effect ( =", sig_factors$Coefficient[i], 
          "RMB, p =", sig_factors$PValue[i], ")\n")
    }
  } else {
    cat("No Significant Influencing Factors\n")
  }
  cat("\n")
}

strong_area_effect <- area_coefficients %>% 
  filter(significance == "Significant" & estimate > 0) %>%
  arrange(-estimate) %>% head(3)

if(nrow(strong_area_effect) > 0) {
  cat("   - Area-Sensitive Districts:", paste(strong_area_effect$District, collapse = ", "), "\n")
  cat("     (In these districts, area increase has the most significant price enhancement effect)\n")
}
